Angola Considering Penalties for Tax Evasion, to Simplify Taxation System

-- B y   C a n d i d o   M e n d e s
-- 
2011-06-06T10:37:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/angola-considering-penalties-for-tax-evasion-to-simplify-taxation-system.html
Angola is considering penalties to
try reduce  tax evasion  to boost income from non-oil industries,
Jornal de Angola reported, citing Finance Minister Carlos
Alberto Lopes.  The southern African nation also plans to simplify its tax
system and may give incentives to encourage payment, the Luanda-
based newspaper cited Lopes as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candido Mendes in Luanda at 
 cmendes6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  